00:17:10.040 --> 00:17:11.810 align:middle line:84%
Let's look at some
of your artwork.

00:17:11.810 --> 00:17:14.390 align:middle line:84%
You mentioned some of
the pictures that you do.

00:17:14.390 --> 00:17:17.390 align:middle line:84%
And you can explain to
us what we're looking at.

00:17:17.390 --> 00:17:20.960 align:middle line:84%
>>PADGETT: So that is the
number pi as it expands.

00:17:20.960 --> 00:17:22.095 align:middle line:90%
So what pi is--

00:17:22.095 --> 00:17:24.470 align:middle line:84%
a lot of times people think
it's like this magical thing.

00:17:24.470 --> 00:17:25.819 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's 3.14.

00:17:25.819 --> 00:17:28.010 align:middle line:90%
>>PADGETT: Yes, 3.14159.

00:17:28.010 --> 00:17:31.130 align:middle line:84%
But it actually what
pi is describing

00:17:31.130 --> 00:17:34.670 align:middle line:84%
is this shape forever
getting smoother and smoother

00:17:34.670 --> 00:17:37.460 align:middle line:84%
as it forever approaches a
circle, but never reaches it

00:17:37.460 --> 00:17:40.320 align:middle line:84%
because there's actually no
such thing as a circle anywhere

00:17:40.320 --> 00:17:41.120 align:middle line:90%
in the universe.

00:17:41.120 --> 00:17:43.328 align:middle line:84%
There's no such thing as a
perfect circle or a curve.

00:17:43.328 --> 00:17:45.260 align:middle line:84%
And the way to think
about it is everybody

00:17:45.260 --> 00:17:47.300 align:middle line:84%
who's watching this
right now on a screen,

00:17:47.300 --> 00:17:49.730 align:middle line:84%
your screen is made with
pixels, which are little squares

00:17:49.730 --> 00:17:50.530 align:middle line:90%
or rectangles.

00:17:50.530 --> 00:17:52.280 align:middle line:84%
So you're not seeing
a curve, you're

00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:53.960 align:middle line:84%
seeing an approximation
of a curve.

00:17:53.960 --> 00:17:56.055 align:middle line:84%
And if you look in closely,
you see the zigzag.

00:17:56.055 --> 00:17:58.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How long did it take
you, Jason, to sketch this?

00:17:58.430 --> 00:18:00.380 align:middle line:84%
