understand it.

00:19:18.365 --> 00:19:20.822 align:middle line:84%
Once I say it's the double--
well, if it's a physicist,

00:19:20.822 --> 00:19:22.030 align:middle line:90%
they'll really understand it.

00:19:22.030 --> 00:19:23.920 align:middle line:90%
Mathematicians, it depends.

00:19:23.920 --> 00:19:26.230 align:middle line:84%
Everything is becoming
so specific nowadays.

00:19:26.230 --> 00:19:28.610 align:middle line:84%
Some mathematicians aren't
familiar with the double slit

00:19:28.610 --> 00:19:29.410 align:middle line:90%
test.

00:19:29.410 --> 00:19:30.790 align:middle line:90%
But I would think most are.

00:19:30.790 --> 00:19:32.350 align:middle line:90%
It's such a famous experiment.

00:19:32.350 --> 00:19:34.390 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Have you been
put under a microscope

00:19:34.390 --> 00:19:35.973 align:middle line:90%
